            "body": "> a way to ask if a path is a filesystem root\n\n`isroot` appears unrelated to `vim.fs.root()`, so we might want to find a different name. Maybe ~~`istop`~~ (edit: could be confused with \"stop\"), idk.\n\n> new additions to `vim.fs` need one simple, cross-platform, and _new_ behavior that isn't trivial to write a wrapper for\n\nTo be clear, `vim.fs` is intended as a single unified interface, but we [declined things like](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31361#issuecomment-2503885558) `fs.exists` until we have exhausted the more urgent gaps. \"trivial wrappers\" can be documented meanwhile.",
